# CLAUDE.md — Kevin's Development Environment

## Session Startup
1. Read project-level `CLAUDE.md` and `tasks/lessons.md` if they exist
2. Read `tasks/todo.md` — resume where you left off
3. Greet briefly, mention active tasks if any

## Environment
- **Machine:** Mac Mini M4 (16GB RAM), macOS
- **Node:** v24.13.0 | **Package manager:** npm/pnpm
- **Shell:** zsh | **Editor:** Claude Code + Cursor + OpenClaw agents
- **Multi-agent:** OpenClaw (35+ agents) | **Tasks:** Paperclip API at localhost:3110

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict mode. ESM only. Functional style preferred.
- No unnecessary comments. Code is self-documenting.
- Error handling: fail fast, throw early, catch at boundaries.
- Tests: Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E).

## Workflow

### Spec-Based Development (ALL features >1 day)
1. **Spec first:** Ask 5-7 questions using AskUserQuestion → write `tasks/spec-YYYYMMDD.md`
2. **New session:** Execute from spec in fresh context (clean cache)
3. **Plan mode** for any task with 3+ steps or architecture decisions

### Subagent Strategy
- Use subagents liberally — keep main context clean
- One task per subagent. Parallel when independent.
- Never switch models mid-session (use subagents for different model needs)

### Verification (MANDATORY before marking done)
- [ ] Feature works end-to-end (Playwright screenshot or test output)
- [ ] No TypeScript errors (`npx tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] No console errors (check browser/logs)
- [ ] Committed with conventional commit message
- [ ] Lessons captured in `tasks/lessons.md` if corrections were made

### Self-Improvement
- After ANY correction: update `tasks/lessons.md` immediately
- Review lessons at session start
- Write rules that prevent the same mistake twice

## Task System Routing
- **Building software (personal projects)** → **Linear `linear` MCP (k3v80 workspace, CC- team)**
  - `mywifi-redesign` → CC / MyWiFi Redesign
  - `guestnetworks-mcp` → CC / GuestNetworks MCP
  - `dmhub-platform` → CC / DMHub Platform
  - Other dev work → CC / Infra & Tooling
- **MyWiFi platform code (staff-tracked)** → **Linear `linear-gn` MCP (Guest Networks workspace)**
  - Bugs, features, and fixes that GN staff also work on
  - Use `linear-gn` MCP for these — different workspace, different team
- **Branch naming:** `cc-{number}-{slug}` · **Commits:** reference `CC-42` · **PR title:** include `CC-42`
- **Marketing/biz/ops** → **Paperclip** (via OpenClaw agents + ACP only). Never create dev tasks in Paperclip.

## Core Principles
- **Simplicity First.** Minimal code, minimal impact.
- **No Laziness.** Root causes only. Senior developer standards.
- **Research Before Build.** Check npm, GitHub, existing libs first.

